    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>No. 114.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 16,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[The Secretary of State refers to his telegram of the 4th instant expressive
                        of the President’s wishes as to early trials, and states that the President,
                        though desirous of not seeming unreasonable, would be relieved if, without
                        having to wait for general action regarding coercion act cases, he could
                        inform Congress that his request regarding the Americans has been complied
                        with.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
